- "diverse array of skilled staff" means more than two types of staff, including those with a BSc in Nursing;
- "essential equipment" and "robust infrastructure" mean more than one type of each, and all must be available;
- "rich tapestry of health services" refers to communities with more than two types of health facilities;
- "average capacity to serve more than 50 individuals" means the average facility capacity in the community exceeds 50.

- A facility's capacity can influence the number of services it can offer.;
- The availability of staff and equipment is crucial for a facility to provide services.;
- The term "services" refers to healthcare services such as maternal health delivery and emergency transport.

- "blossoming facilities" refers to facilities that are thriving and well-staffed;
- "exceeds the average number of full-time staff" means having more full-time staff than the average number of full-time staff across all facilities;
- "a plethora of services" indicates a large number of services offered.

